players.name: Hugo Marques
players.summary: Hugo Miguel Barreto Henriques Marques is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Girabola club Atlético Petróleos de Luanda and the Angola national team.

players.name: Antonio Dominique
players.summary: Antonio Signori Nymi Dominique is a professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Swiss club Étoile Carouge.

players.name: Neblú
players.summary: Adilson Cipriano da Cruz is an Angolan footballer who goes by the nickname Neblú and plays as a goalkeeper for 1º de Agosto.

players.name: Núrio Fortuna
players.summary: Núrio Domingos Matias Fortuna is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a left-back for Super League Greece club Volos, on loan from Gent, and the Angola national team.

players.name: Jonathan Buatu
players.summary: Jonathan Buatu Mananga is a professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Portuguese Primeira Liga club Gil Vicente. Born in Belgium, he represents the Angola national team.

players.name: Clinton Mata
players.summary: Clinton Mukoni Mata Pedro Lourenço is a professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Ligue 1 club Lyon. Born in Belgium, he played for the Angola national team, having made eight appearances.

players.name: David Carmo
players.summary: David Mota Veiga Teixeira do Carmo is a professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for La Liga club Oviedo, on loan from Premier League club Nottingham Forest, and the Angola national team.

players.name: Kialonda Gaspar
players.summary: Esmevânio Kialonda Gaspar, sometimes known as just Gaspar, is an Angolan footballer who plays as a centre-back for Italian Serie A club Lecce.

players.name: Tó Carneiro
players.summary: Augusto de Jesus Corte Real Carneiro, commonly known as Tó Carneiro, is an Angolan professional football player who plays for Petro de Luanda and the Angolan national team.

players.name: Eddie Afonso
players.summary: Eddie Marcos Melo Afonso is an Angolan footballer who plays as a left-back for Petro de Luanda and the Angola national team.

players.name: Rui Modesto
players.summary: Rui Manuel Muati Modesto is a footballer who plays as a winger for Italian Serie A club Udinese. Born in Portugal, he represents the Angola national team. Initially a defender in his native Portugal, Modesto moved to a more attacking role after moving to Finland.

players.name: Pedro Bondo
players.summary: Pedro Bondo Francisco is an Angolan professional football player who plays as a left-back for Primeira Liga club Famalicão and the Angola national team.

players.name: Maestro
players.summary: Maestro is an honorific title of respect, sometimes abbreviated Mo. The term is most commonly used in the context of Western classical music and opera, in line with the ubiquitous use of Italian musical terms. The feminine form of the word is maestra.

players.name: Beni Mukendi
players.summary: Benedito "Beni" Mambuene Mukendi is an Angolan footballer who plays as a midfielder for Vitória and the Angola national team.

players.name: Fredy
players.summary:
Fredy is a given name, and may refer to:Fredy Bareiro, Paraguayan football player
Fredy Barth, Swiss racing driver
Fredy Clue, Swedish artist and musician
Fredy Glanzmann, Swiss Nordic combined skier
Fredy Hernández, Colombian race walker
Fredy Montero Colombian footballer with Sounders FC
Fredy Otárola, Peruvian politician
Fredy Perlman (1934–1985), author, publisher and activist
Fredy Reyna (1917–2001), Venezuelan musician, arranger and performer
Fredy Schmidtke, track cyclist

players.name: Randy Nteka
players.summary: Randy Nteka is a professional footballer who plays for La Liga club Rayo Vallecano. Mainly an attacking midfielder, he can also play as a forward. Born in France, he represents Angola internationally.

players.name: Manuel Keliano
players.summary: Manuel Keliano is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Russian club Akhmat Grozny and the Angola national team.

players.name: Show
players.summary: Show or The Show may refer to:

players.name: Mário Balbúrdia
players.summary: Mário César Azevedo Alves Balbúrdia is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as midfielder for Boluspor and the Angola national team.

players.name: Felício Milson
players.summary: Felício Mendes João Milson is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a winger for Serbian SuperLiga club Red Star Belgrade and the Angola national team.

players.name: M'Bala Nzola
players.summary: M'Bala Nzola is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a forward for Serie A club Pisa on loan from Fiorentina, and the Angola national team.

players.name: Gelson Dala
players.summary: Jacinto Muondo "Gelson" Dala is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as an attacking midfielder or a forward for Al-Wakrah in the Qatar Stars League.

players.name: Ary Papel
players.summary: Manuel David Afonso, known as Ary Papel, is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as winger for in Libyan Premier League club Al Akhdar.

players.name: Manuel Benson
players.summary: Manuel Benson Hedilazio is a professional footballer who plays as a winger for EFL Championship club Swansea City on loan from Premier League club Burnley. Born in Belgium, he plays for the Angola national team.

players.name: Zito Luvumbo
players.summary: Zito André Sebastião Luvumbo is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a winger for Serie A club Cagliari and the Angola national team.

players.name: Mabululu
players.summary: Agostinho Cristóvão Paciência, commonly known as Mabululu, is Angolan professional footballer who plays as a striker for Libyan Premier League club Al Ahli Tripoli. He played at the 2014 FIFA World Cup qualification.

players.name: Chico Banza
players.summary: Francisco Gonçalves Sacalumbo, commonly known as Chico Banza, or simply Chico, is an Angolan professional footballer who plays as a winger for Zamalek.
